locality:  NA, occurrenceRemarks: The image contains a commin plant that I have positively identified as being within the Genus of Galax. The plant is green wit a large simple leaf and rigid edges, and hs one leaf per stem and is in a small cluster (numerous plants of the same species are within the image). This plant is located in a deciduous forest, obscured location, withun partial to complete shade, and wet to moist. Additionally, the leaf is more rounded but seems as if it is consistent of a geart shaoe but with two lobes. This is a herbaceous and evergreen plant that is codified as perennial and is common within the regions that I have identified it within; the plant can be flund in the Appalachian mountians (the general region in which this plant was located) and at regions up to 1,500 meters. I believe that this plats taxonomic nomenclature is Galax urceolata., verbatimLocality: North Carolina, US

locality:  NA, occurrenceRemarks: Occoneechee Mountain State Natural Area. High scenic views and mountain trails await you at Occoneechee Mountain State Natural Area. This Piedmont monadnock has been recognized as one of the most important natural areas in the Triangle. It is the highest point in Orange County at 867 feet, and the oak forest, pond, field, heath bluff, and river habitats found on the mountain support species that are rare and significant in this region. With 190 acres of land and nearly three miles of trails, visitors can experience a wide variety of the area's natural surroundings and wildlife., verbatimLocality: 501–537 Dimmocks Mill Rd, Hillsborough, NC, US

habitat: W-facing slope under and oak tree. Formerly a dairy farm, the plants on a steep slope with cliffs that had been fenced off to keep the cows out. Deep within a natural area.
